	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=927'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#330066;'>inoffensive_name</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Philosopher<br>
			
				Posts: 1660<br>
				
				Registered: 03-01-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=927'>







<img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v375/rhesusmonkeyboy/EverQuest/smallMe.jpg" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Magicians&message.id=629#M629">1</a> of 21
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 503 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			So, I don't know why, but I looked at "Screaming Terror" that necromancers get, and thought it was a pretty weak explanation of necro's being capable of mezzing. The theory being, I guess, the things are terrified and just stand there screaming, though they may forget what they're screaming about.<br><br>Once I got over class envy <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> that they get fear and snare and mez, I thought about poor mages lack of helping with the shizzle hits the fan ( wizzies evac, ench AoE mez & stun, nec's mez ) and then I thought of this while we got a gross over-pull in a Lost Dungeon of Norrath.<br><br><blockquote>I think it'd be cool if mages could summon pet, a la Rage of Zomm, however, this would ( at low levels ) attack the targetted NPC ... but, high taunt, low low damage. <br><br>So that say there was one fearsome beast clobbering the evac'er ... you cast this thing and it irritates and takes aggro off the mob, but without helping you kill it in a timely manner.</blockquote><br><br>Then I figured, like mez, at higher levels, maybe it's an self-AoE spell ... so if there were 5 monsters around you'd have the same limit, but a couple pets would show up and distract folks while they ran / evac'd / emergency healed, et al.<br><br>I'm not clever or devious enough to figure out how to make it unexploitable, but I figure if you could combine low damage with good taunt-ability that'd work. Not so good that you'd nuke from a mile away, you know. <br><br><b><i>But that way mages would not be the only intelligence caster that can't help calm things down in a bad situation.</i></b><br><br>Possible, plausible?<br><br>~inoffensive
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							~inoffensive<hr color="blue"><table border="1"><th colspan="2">Retired</th><tr><td colspan="2" align="center">Looking for Patch Message Archives? <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/updates/recent_updates.jsp">Recent Updates</a> or perhaps <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board?board.id=Crier">Crier Forums</a> has them!</td></tr><tr align="center"><td><a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/search?advanced=true">Advanced Search</a>es are awesome.</td><td><a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=124427#M124427">I'll take a loot into this.  ~ <font color="33CC00"><b>Absor</b></font></a></td></tr></table>
							</div>
								
