<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Ashlanne wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Interesting idea... I would like to see what the other mage's think about this before passing it along...</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>I would run this past the enchaters too. Mezz plus charm are the class defining abilities of enchanters. This spell essentially allows mages to CC unmezable mobs. I think most enchanters would see this as a threat, because there would be a&nbsp;class that could do CC while avoiding the issues of MR or level restrictions. For example mages could&nbsp;then CC Grieg's guards, while enchanters could not.&nbsp;Number one on the class balance list&nbsp;from Enchanters was their ability to do CC was being taken over by bards and that to many mobs were unaffected by their mainline spells.&nbsp;</P>
<P>Pet mez is alreay a great suppliment to CC.</P>
