			<DIV>Interesting idea...you've inspired me <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>How about a pet that is a Decoy.&nbsp; Good HPs, very high AoE taunt,. limited duration (30 secs), when the 'shizzle hits the fan' and escape is the best/only option, the mage casts this spell and the pet when summoned starts AoE taunting (big range) and tehn runs off away from the mage as fast and as far as it can get before the 30 secs are up or the mage gets Evac'd or gates/zones out.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Prevention of exploiting this somehow is the pet taunts EVERYTHING in its range, which is big, and when it poofs all the mobs and the gazillion friends come charging back to smear the mage (and his group) into paste...perhaps to prevent using this as a tool for pulling for AoE groups, all mobs aggro'd by the pet get a 60 second buff that makes them immune to all spells (so once pet poofs after 30 secs, there is a minimum of another 30 secs before anyone could cast a spell on the mobs.)</DIV>
