		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Enchanter Perspective:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I generally find my role is to CC.&nbsp; I&nbsp; know that there are other ways to do it, such as Necro's spells or root parking, but this sounds a little too much like "Let us do what they do" type thinking.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If there's an overpull that's going to wipe the party, then there's going to be an overpull that wipes the party.&nbsp; You die, you get rez'd, you do a CR you move on.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is what makes good pulling, good CC essential to a group.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think this is a decent idea but I'd be afraid of it becoming something that could lead to abuse and shut enchanters out of groups.&nbsp; Why bring an enchanter when the uber mage pet can handle CC that goes crazy?&nbsp; If it can taunt like a warrior why bother having a warrior?&nbsp; Just send in the "Decoy" let it taunt and then chain cast them as the artilery opens up.&nbsp; Maybe you let the cleric tank it a bit but then toss in another decoy.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Also if you have insane agro range/ area taunt you start some serious trains that could be nightmarish for other groups.&nbsp; Imagine merrily pounding away in your own area as you see a decoy with 100 orcs running along behind it, right at you.&nbsp; Sure the party that summoned the decoy is safely evacing.. but you're toast!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There are other ways to control agro as a pet class.&nbsp; If you have an earth pet up, he has root.&nbsp; That can help root park a mob so your evac'r can back up.&nbsp; Same with stun on the air pet.&nbsp; If the Evac'r does some savy manuevering he might be able to loose a mob and then&nbsp; hold still enough to evac.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And if too many add's is a problem, make friends with an Enchanter.&nbsp; It's what we're good at.&nbsp; We'll let you have cool pets, you let us have mez.&nbsp; Otherwise we start down a road where you get taunting pets, we start aiming for pets that actually obey commands.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mr. O</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
