		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			MrOsterman, that's not what I'm going for at all. <br>I'm sorry if my posts were unclear<ul><li>I don't want a pet that would hold taunt no matter what other PCs did</li><br><li>I'm not going for a "let us do what they do" exactly ... my mage can escape from danger at level 55 the same as he did at level 4 ... Gate ... that's it</li></ul><br><br>I say this nicely, but go back, I just had a situation come up and thought, "Oh, this idea would add groupability to mage's as well as address a common complaint ... pet's are weak in a pinch." There's folks who say, "Mage pets are too weak to allow for mage's lack of escape."<br><br>This is true. <br>Literally, all we have is gate. We're the only intelligence caster who only have gate.<br><br>I'm guessing with the negativity the idea already died but all I was suggesting was<ul><li>A weirdo type of pet, to allow mages a tad more than "run" in a bad situation ... which is literally what I've done at times ... and all I have ... especially when travelling</li><br><li>By extension, I thought, "Oh, this could be augmented at later levels to be something to make mage's group friendly!"</li><br><li>I don't want, and stated earlier, I don't want a pet to trivialize combat ... a pet that you could nuke from a distance while it decoyed would just be lame ... which is why I talked about a pet that could gain aggro if you weren't doing anything aggro-vating</li></ul>I love my mage, but think he needs a little tweak, is all ... I thought this would be nice, but wanted folks to talk about problems it had, Ashlanne seemed intrigued.<br><br>I'm not trying to be negative, or an internet geek / jerk who quotes but <blockquote><i>Why bring an enchanter when the uber mage pet can handle CC that goes crazy?</i></blockquote>I never intended to even hint at an uber mage pet that can handle CC that goes crazy ... it occurred to me in a CC that went crazy ... like a back-up plan ... I don't think an insanely low-damage pet that hung around ( for a finite random duration ) "bugging" a mob, that <i>could</i> gain the attention of an NPC would obliterate the need for enchanters and bards. <br><br><blockquote><i>If it can taunt like a warrior why bother having a warrior?  Just send in the "Decoy" let it taunt and then chain cast them as the artilery opens up. </i></blockquote>Again, I don't want that to happen. <br><br>Come to think of it, to a degree current pets taunt like a warrior. <br><br>In the sense that pets have a "Taunting attack, master" ... look earlier and I stated that I'd not want a pet that would taunt while you nuked with impunity. That'd just be lame. I'm not insinuating you think that's cool, I'm just saying, I believe I agree that that'd be lame, I certainly don't want that.<br><br><blockquote><i>Imagine merrily pounding away in your own area as you see a decoy with 100 orcs running along behind it, right at you.</i></blockquote>Very good point. I imagined it as being pets ( say 3 or 4 at the high level "AoE" level ) that would just stand in front of the mobs and attempt their stupid-low damage "taunt proc that has level limitations and/or a save vs something" to buy you and others in your party time to do something.<br><br>I never stated that ... but I didn't mean a decoy ( like jets' electronic counter measures ) that'd run off and taunt as it ran off.  It's a subtle difference, but it would certainly make a huge difference.<br><br><blockquote><i>If you have an earth pet up, he has root.  That can help root park a mob so your evac'r can back up.  Same with stun on the air pet.  If the Evac'r does some savy manuevering he might be able to loose a mob and then  hold still enough to evac.</i></blockquote>I do do that. It works every once in a while ... but I've had pets get obliterated off-tanking too, where I think a "mez" pet would've helped.<br><br><blockquote><i>We'll let you have cool pets, you let us have mez.  </i></blockquote>Via charm, you do have super cool pets, yes there is risk, but you have irrestible magic debuffs, roots, stuns, and mem blurs to help that a tad.<br><br>Anyhow, judging the "flack" I'm guessing my idea sucks ... which is cool ... I just wanted to throw it out there and see what happened. Partially what I thought would happen did .. but I've had worse experiences with and within EverQuest.<br><br><font size="+1">Good luck all, and see you in Norrath</font><br><br>inoffensively,<br>~inoffensive_name<br><br>PS I'm a magician who <i>hates</i> solo'ing ... ask my guildies.<br><br>For rizzle.<br><br><img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>
