<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
inoffensive_name wrote:<BR><BR><BR>Anyhow, judging the "flack" I'm guessing my idea sucks ... which is cool ... I just wanted to throw it out there and see what happened. Partially what I thought would happen did .. but I've had worse experiences with and within EverQuest.<BR><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>I wouldn't say "Sucks".&nbsp; I'd just say... not needed, in my opinion.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I also know that I NEED to get out there and work on my charm.&nbsp; I find it not generally worth the risk.&nbsp; I mainly play in pick up groups and with charm if the spell breaks when&nbsp;I'm not ready then there's major heck to pay and root, mem blur, etc are all useless when you're being beat like a bohdran in an Irish Band playing a jig at a tempo which they call "More then Indian Hot".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm not sure how to make Mage's more group friendly myself, if you feel like you're being left out of the higher levels.&nbsp; I haven't played up enough to get to the point where I'm dealing with out-and-out unmezzable monsters.&nbsp; Of course my gut reaction is that if I can't mez it, I ain't going to try to charm it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So take that for what it is.&nbsp; Heck I'd even settle for having monsters nerfed while under charm as a "balancing" to keep our place as CC.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's a terrible idea, honestly, but it would have be very careful to avoid making another class less valuable.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Sorry if I seemed grumpy.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mr. O</DIV>
