<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Magicians&message.id=665#M665">18</a> of 21
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 263 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>On this subject, how about having a relatively quick casting spell that changes the nuke of the pet, even the earth pet's root attack, &nbsp;into an PBAoE root of limited duration (say 12 seconds),&nbsp;sizeable radius (say 30 feet) AND the pet goes *poof* once it does the PBAoE. In effect, the death of the pet puts a movement hold on all mobs around it and if the mage (and party) hasn't done something to get out or engage in effective CC by the time the AoE root expires, they will be in big trouble.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In effect, the magician sacrifices his pet in an attempt to buy some time. The limitation is that the magician has to have his elemental pet up in order to do this and it will go *poof* each time he does it. That should help with curbing abusive use of this effect and limit encroachment on the CC turf of Enchanters. I think. Root durations and the size of the area of effect could be adjusted, what I put in was just a initial suggestion.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This could be expanded to include pet suicide PBAoE stuns and mezzes, etc. etc.&nbsp; But in each case, the pet must die. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
